The paper deals with information complexity and its relation to tension, which are both concepts in information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the trade-off between communication in two directions in a 2-party protocol, which falls under cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of tension to bound the 2-dimensional region also involves concepts from cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper highlights tension as a fundamental measure of correlation between random variables, which is a topic in cs.LG (Machine Learning).
